# Attribute reference

Every `honeyhive.*` attribute name accepted by the HoneyHive ingestion
pipeline is defined here. Each attribute has:

- an **`id`** — the fully qualified wire-format name, including the
  `honeyhive.` prefix and any bucket segment
- a **`type`** — `string`, `int`, `double`, `boolean`, `string[]`, or an
  enum
- a **`stability` tier** — `stable` or `development`
- a one-sentence **brief**, plus longer notes and example values where
  helpful

Stable attributes are part of HoneyHive's long-term contract; development
attributes may change before a major release. Match the tier on each
page before depending on an attribute in production.

